Body:
According to our research, there are misuses about the following servral AsyncTask classes:_x000D_
( in ru.valle.btc. MainActivity.java)_x000D_
```_x000D_
    @Nullable_x000D_
    private AsyncTask<Void, Void, KeyPair> addressGenerateTask;_x000D_
    @Nullable_x000D_
    private AsyncTask<Void, Void, GenerateTransactionResult> generateTransactionTask;_x000D_
    @Nullable_x000D_
    private AsyncTask<Void, Void, KeyPair> switchingCompressionTypeTask;_x000D_
    @Nullable_x000D_
    private AsyncTask<Void, Void, KeyPair> switchingSegwitTask;_x000D_
    @Nullable_x000D_
    private AsyncTask<Void, Void, KeyPair> decodePrivateKeyTask;_x000D_
    @Nullable_x000D_
    private AsyncTask<Void, Void, Object> bip38Task;_x000D_
    @Nullable_x000D_
    private AsyncTask<Void, Void, ArrayList<UnspentOutputInfo>> decodeUnspentOutputsInfoTask;_x000D_
```_x000D_
_x000D_
The problems are:_x000D_
1. They are anonymous inner classes. They hold strong reference to the GUI element of Activity( MainActivity ), which can lead to memory leak when the Activity is destroyed and the AsyncTask did not finish_x000D_
2. Their instances are cancelled before the Activity is destroyed. But in the doInBackground method there are for or while loop without the call of isCancelled() . These loops may not be able to terminate when the task is cancelled. This will cause waste of resources or even flashback_x000D_
_x000D_
I think we can make following changes to fix the misuse problems:_x000D_
1. I think the GUI-related fields should be wrapped into WeakReference. Take _x000D_
`private final MainActivity _context` as example, it can be changed to `private final WeakReference<MainActivity> _context`._x000D_
2. Every loop should check the status of AsyncTask to break the loop._x000D_
```_x000D_
while(condition1){_x000D_
     if(isCancelled()){_x000D_
          break;_x000D_
     }_x000D_
     //blablabla…_x000D_
     while(condition2){_x000D_
         if(isCancelled()){_x000D_
              break;_x000D_
         }_x000D_
         //blablabla…_x000D_
     }_x000D_
}_x000D_
```_x000D_
_x000D_
These are my suggestions above, thank you.
